---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

// FAQ data organized by categories - General Questions FIRST
const faqCategories = [
  {
    id: 'general',
    title: 'General Questions',
    icon: `<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8.228 9c.549-1.165 2.03-2 3.772-2 2.21 0 4 1.343 4 3 0 1.4-1.278 2.575-3.006 2.907-.542.104-.994.54-.994 1.093m0 3h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" /></svg>`,
    questions: [
      {
        q: "How can I book an appointment?",
        a: "You can book an appointment online through the Notino platform, or by phone at +36 1 300 9414. For online booking, select your desired treatment, location, and time slot. We'll send you a confirmation by email."
      },
      {
        q: "Where are the salons located?",
        a: "We welcome you at two locations: Beautyflow Buda (1116 Budapest, Vegyesz u. 1.) and Beautyflow Pest (1135 Budapest, Reitter Ferenc u. 90.). Both salons are easily accessible by public transport and car."
      },
      {
        q: "What are the opening hours?",
        a: "Beautyflow Buda: Monday-Friday 08:00-20:00, Saturday 10:00-20:00, Sunday 10:00-19:00. Beautyflow Pest: Monday-Friday 08:00-18:00, Saturday 10:00-20:00, Sunday closed."
      },
      {
        q: "Is there a free consultation?",
        a: "Yes, we provide a free consultation before every treatment! During the consultation, we assess your needs, answer your questions, and create a personalized treatment plan. You can book an appointment on our free consultation page."
      },
      {
        q: "What payment methods do you accept?",
        a: "We accept both cash and card payments. For larger treatment packages, we also offer installment payment options. Please inquire about the details at the salon."
      },
      {
        q: "Is there parking available?",
        a: "There is parking available near both of our salons. At the Buda salon, street parking and a nearby parking garage are available. At the Pest salon, street parking is also possible. You can find detailed directions on the location page."
      },
      {
        q: "Can I cancel or reschedule my appointment?",
        a: "Yes, you can cancel or reschedule your appointment free of charge up to 24 hours before the treatment. Please notify us by phone or online. Cancellations within 24 hours may incur a cancellation fee."
      },
      {
        q: "Can I purchase gift vouchers?",
        a: "Yes, we offer gift vouchers for any treatment or any amount. Gift vouchers can be purchased at our salons and make an excellent gift for birthdays, name days, or any occasion."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 'laser-hair-removal',
    title: 'Laser Hair Removal',
    icon: `<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" /></svg>`,
    questions: [
      {
        q: "What is a diode laser and how does it differ from other laser types?",
        a: "A diode laser is a laser technology that operates at 808 nm wavelength and is excellent for targeted treatment of hair follicles. Compared to other lasers (alexandrite, Nd:YAG), diode laser is more effective at treating melanin-rich hair while being gentler on the skin. The professional diode laser devices used at Beautyflow salons feature the latest cooling technology, making the treatment more comfortable."
      },
      {
        q: "How many treatments are needed for lasting results?",
        a: "Generally, 6-10 treatments are needed for lasting results, at 4-6 week intervals. The number of sessions depends on the size of the treated area, hair density and color, and individual hormonal status. After completing the treatments, 1-2 maintenance sessions per year are recommended."
      },
      {
        q: "Is laser hair removal painful?",
        a: "Modern diode laser devices have built-in cooling systems that significantly reduce discomfort. Most patients experience a mild stinging or warm sensation. Sensitivity varies between individuals, but the treatment is generally well-tolerated. Numbing cream can be applied if needed."
      },
      {
        q: "What skin types is the treatment suitable for?",
        a: "Diode laser hair removal is suitable for almost all skin types, from light to darker skin tones (Fitzpatrick I-V). The most effective results are achieved with dark hair and lighter skin, but modern devices can be safely used on darker skin as well. The treatment is less effective on blonde, red, or gray hair."
      },
      {
        q: "What should I do before and after the treatment?",
        a: "Before treatment: Avoid sun exposure and self-tanners for 2 weeks, don't epilate or wax for 4 weeks, shave the hair 24 hours before the treatment. After treatment: Avoid sun exposure and use sunscreen, don't use saunas or hot baths for 48 hours, avoid intense exercise for 24 hours, and moisturize the skin regularly."
      },
      {
        q: "Are there any side effects of the treatment?",
        a: "Laser hair removal is generally a safe procedure. Temporary side effects may include mild redness, swelling, or sensitivity, which usually subside within a few hours. In rare cases, pigmentation changes or blistering may occur, so professional treatment and following aftercare advice are important."
      },
      {
        q: "How often should treatments be repeated?",
        a: "Treatments are generally performed every 4-6 weeks, following the hair growth cycle. For the face, more frequent intervals (3-4 weeks) are recommended, while for the body, longer intervals (5-6 weeks) are advised. After completing the treatment series, 1-2 maintenance sessions per year are sufficient."
      },
      {
        q: "When will I see results?",
        a: "Initial results are visible after just 1-2 treatments: hair becomes thinner and sparser. The treated hairs fall out 1-3 weeks after the treatment. Lasting results are achieved after completing the full treatment series (6-10 sessions)."
      },
      {
        q: "Can the treatment be done during pregnancy or breastfeeding?",
        a: "We do not recommend laser hair removal during pregnancy and breastfeeding. Although there is no evidence that it is harmful, following the principle of caution and due to hormonal changes, it is advisable to postpone the treatment."
      },
      {
        q: "Can the treatment be done on intimate areas?",
        a: "Yes, treatment of intimate areas (bikini line, Brazilian, full intimate) is popular and safe. The cooling system of modern devices is especially important in these sensitive areas. Our specialists perform the treatment discreetly and professionally."
      },
      {
        q: "Can men also use this service?",
        a: "Absolutely! Laser hair removal is increasingly popular among men. Common areas include: back, shoulders, chest, abdomen, and face (beard line). Men's hair is generally thicker, so a few extra treatments may be needed."
      },
      {
        q: "How much does laser hair removal cost?",
        a: "Prices depend on the size of the treated area. Smaller areas (underarms, upper lip) start from a few thousand forints, larger areas (full legs, back) are more expensive. We offer significant discounts with our package deals. For exact prices, visit our Prices page or request a personalized quote."
      },
      {
        q: "Can the treatment be done over a tattoo?",
        a: "Laser hair removal CANNOT be performed over a tattoo because the laser may target the ink, which can cause burns or discoloration of the tattoo. Tattooed areas must be avoided during the treatment."
      },
      {
        q: "Is it safe around moles and freckles?",
        a: "Moles and other pigmented skin lesions must be avoided during treatment. Before the laser treatment, our specialist will assess your skin and mark the areas to avoid. For large or suspicious moles, dermatological consultation is recommended."
      },
      {
        q: "What happens if I miss a treatment?",
        a: "Missing one session does not significantly affect the results, but regular treatment is more effective. If you take a longer break, hair growth may restart, and more follow-up treatments may be needed. Try to maintain the recommended 4-6 week interval."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 'hydrabeauty',
    title: 'HydraBeauty Facial',
    icon: `<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 21a4 4 0 01-4-4V5a2 2 0 012-2h4a2 2 0 012 2v12a4 4 0 01-4 4zm0 0h12a2 2 0 002-2v-4a2 2 0 00-2-2h-2.343M11 7.343l1.657-1.657a2 2 0 012.828 0l2.829 2.829a2 2 0 010 2.828l-8.486 8.485M7 17h.01" /></svg>`,
    questions: [
      {
        q: "What is HydraBeauty treatment?",
        a: "HydraBeauty is a multi-step, non-invasive facial treatment that provides cleansing, exfoliation, skin tightening, and intense hydration in a single session. The treatment uses special vacuum technology that deeply cleanses pores and delivers active ingredients into the skin."
      },
      {
        q: "What skin problems is HydraBeauty recommended for?",
        a: "HydraBeauty is excellent for: dehydrated skin, enlarged pores and blackheads, dull and tired skin, fine lines, uneven skin tone, and acne-prone skin. It is recommended for almost all skin types and is also suitable for sensitive skin."
      },
      {
        q: "Is HydraBeauty treatment painful?",
        a: "No, the treatment is completely painless. Most patients find it pleasant and relaxing. The vacuum cleansing creates a gentle suction effect, but it is not uncomfortable. You can return to your daily activities immediately after the treatment."
      },
      {
        q: "How long does a treatment take?",
        a: "A complete HydraBeauty treatment takes approximately 45-60 minutes. This includes skin preparation, the multi-step treatment, and the finishing care."
      },
      {
        q: "How often is HydraBeauty recommended?",
        a: "For optimal results, 1-2 treatments per month are recommended. For intensive skin renewal, 4-6 treatments at 2-week intervals are initially recommended, followed by monthly maintenance treatments. Our specialist will create a personalized treatment plan based on individual needs and skin condition."
      },
      {
        q: "When will I see results?",
        a: "Results are visible immediately! Your skin will be more radiant, hydrated, and fresher after just the first treatment. Lasting results and improvement of deeper problems are achieved after several treatments."
      },
      {
        q: "Is there any recovery time after the treatment?",
