      },
      {
        q: "Can it be combined with other treatments?",
        a: "Yes, HydraBeauty can be excellently combined with other treatments, such as: LED light therapy, mesotherapy, and wrinkle filling. Our specialist will provide information about combined treatments during the consultation."
      },
      {
        q: "Is it suitable for sensitive skin?",
        a: "Yes, HydraBeauty is particularly gentle and also suitable for sensitive skin. The intensity of the treatment can be adjusted, and the serums used can also be customized according to individual skin conditions."
      },
      {
        q: "Can the treatment be done during pregnancy?",
        a: "HydraBeauty is generally safe, but it is advisable to consult with the treating specialist during pregnancy. Some intensive active ingredients (e.g., retinol) should be avoided, but the cleansing and hydrating steps can generally be performed."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 'tattoo-removal',
    title: 'Tattoo Removal',
    icon: `<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 7l-.867 12.142A2 2 0 0116.138 21H7.862a2 2 0 01-1.995-1.858L5 7m5 4v6m4-6v6m1-10V4a1 1 0 00-1-1h-4a1 1 0 00-1 1v3M4 7h16" /></svg>`,
    questions: [
      {
        q: "How does laser tattoo removal work?",
        a: "During laser tattoo removal, the laser uses high-energy light pulses to break down ink particles in the skin into tiny pieces. These particles are then naturally removed by the body's immune system over the following weeks. The treatment is a safe and effective way to remove unwanted tattoos."
      },
      {
        q: "How many treatments are needed to remove a tattoo?",
        a: "The number of treatments needed depends on the size, color, depth, and age of the tattoo. Generally, 6-12 treatments are required, at 6-8 week intervals. Amateur tattoos fade faster, while professional, colored tattoos require more treatments."
      },
      {
        q: "Is tattoo removal painful?",
        a: "The treatment involves some discomfort; many compare the sensation to a rubber band snapping against the skin. Modern lasers have cooling systems that reduce pain. For larger areas or more sensitive patients, numbing cream can be applied."
      },
      {
        q: "What color tattoos can be removed?",
        a: "Black and dark blue tattoos are the easiest to remove. Green, light blue, and purple colors require more treatments. Yellow, orange, and white colors are the most difficult. With modern multiwave lasers, almost all colors can be treated."
      },
      {
        q: "Will there be scarring after the treatment?",
        a: "With professional treatment and proper aftercare, the risk of scarring is minimal. The laser targets the ink, not the skin. It is important to allow adequate healing time between treatments and follow expert instructions."
      },
      {
        q: "When will I see results?",
        a: "Tattoo fading occurs gradually, treatment by treatment. The first significant change is usually visible after 2-3 treatments. After each treatment, the body works for 6-8 weeks to remove the ink particles."
      },
      {
        q: "Is there recovery time after the treatment?",
        a: "Redness, swelling, and blistering may occur in the treated area for 1-2 weeks - this is a normal reaction. The area may be sensitive for 2-4 weeks. Avoid sun exposure, swimming, and intense sports during healing."
      },
      {
        q: "Can permanent makeup be removed?",
        a: "Yes, permanent makeup (eyebrows, eyelids, lips) can also be removed with laser, but these require special treatment due to the sensitivity of the area. It's important to know that certain permanent makeup pigments may oxidize and darken at the first treatment."
      },
      {
        q: "Can a fresh tattoo be removed?",
        a: "We recommend starting treatment of a fresh tattoo at least 6-8 weeks after the tattoo was done, so the skin can fully heal. New tattoos are often easier to remove because the ink has not penetrated as deeply."
      },
      {
        q: "How much does tattoo removal cost?",
        a: "The price depends on the size of the tattoo. Treatment of smaller tattoos (e.g., 5x5 cm) costs approximately 15-25 thousand forints per session, larger areas are proportionally more expensive. We offer better prices with package deals."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 'permanent-makeup',
    title: 'Permanent Makeup',
    icon: `<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15.232 5.232l3.536 3.536m-2.036-5.036a2.5 2.5 0 113.536 3.536L6.5 21.036H3v-3.572L16.732 3.732z" /></svg>`,
    questions: [
      {
        q: "What is permanent makeup?",
        a: "Permanent makeup (cosmetic tattooing) is a cosmetic tattooing technique that results in natural-looking, long-lasting makeup. Special pigments applied to the upper layers of the skin can enhance eyebrows, eyes, and lips. The results last 1-3 years and then gradually fade."
      },
      {
        q: "What permanent makeup techniques exist?",
        a: "Popular techniques include: Microblading (eyebrow hair strokes), Ombre/powder brows, Combination brows, Eyeliner tattooing, and Lip contour and lip tattooing. Each technique has its advantages, and the choice depends on individual needs and facial features."
      },
      {
        q: "Is permanent makeup painful?",
        a: "We apply numbing cream before the treatment, so pain is minimal. Most people feel a slight scratching or pressure sensation. Sensitivity varies between individuals; the sensation may be more intense for lips and eyelids."
      },
      {
        q: "How long does permanent makeup last?",
        a: "Duration varies between 1-3 years, depending on skin type, the technique applied, pigment color, and lifestyle. It fades faster on oilier skin. A touch-up treatment is recommended once a year to maintain perfect results."
      },
      {
        q: "What is the healing process like?",
        a: "Healing takes 7-14 days. In the first few days, the color will be more intense, then scabs form and gradually fall off. The final color and shape are visible after 4-6 weeks. Important: do not scratch or soak the area during healing!"
      },
      {
        q: "Is a touch-up required?",
        a: "Yes, a touch-up treatment is recommended 4-6 weeks after the first treatment. This is part of the process and is usually included in the price. During the touch-up, we refine the shape, replace any pigment that may have fallen out, and finalize the result."
      },
      {
        q: "Am I suitable for permanent makeup?",
        a: "Permanent makeup is suitable for most people. Contraindications include: pregnancy, breastfeeding, diabetes, blood clotting disorders, epilepsy, active skin conditions, and tendency to keloid scarring. We assess suitability during the consultation."
      },
      {
        q: "How do I choose the right shape and color?",
        a: "During the consultation, our specialist considers your face shape, skin tone, eye color, and personal preferences. Before the tattoo, we draw the shape so you can see and approve it. The color fades by 30-40% after healing."
      },
      {
        q: "Can I apply makeup to my eyebrows after the treatment?",
        a: "Avoid applying makeup to the treated area during healing (7-14 days). After that, you can apply makeup, but the point of permanent makeup is that you'll need little to no makeup. Many people only add to it on special occasions."
      },
      {
        q: "What happens if I don't like the result?",
        a: "The thorough pre-treatment consultation and preliminary shape drawing minimize this risk. If you are still dissatisfied, we can make adjustments during the touch-up appointment. As a last resort, permanent makeup can be removed with laser, although this is a time-consuming process."
      }
    ]
  },
