        a: "For optimal results, 4-6 treatments are recommended at 2-4 week intervals. For maintenance, once a month is sufficient. A single treatment before special events also provides impressive results."
      },
      {
        q: "When will I see results?",
        a: "Results are visible immediately! Your skin will be more radiant, cleaner, and firmer after just the first treatment. Pores contract and skin becomes more even. Due to collagen production stimulation, results continue to improve for weeks."
      },
      {
        q: "Are there any side effects?",
        a: "Carbon Peeling is extremely safe. Mild redness may occur, which usually disappears within a few hours. In rare cases, temporary sensitivity may occur. Sun protection is important after the treatment."
      },
      {
        q: "Can it be combined with other treatments?",
        a: "Yes, it can be excellently combined with other treatments: HydraBeauty (deeper cleansing), LED light therapy, and mesotherapy. Our specialist will provide personalized recommendations for combined treatments."
      },
      {
        q: "Is it suitable for sensitive skin?",
        a: "Carbon Peeling is generally suitable for sensitive skin, but a preliminary consultation is recommended. The treatment intensity can be adjusted. The treatment is contraindicated in cases of active inflammation or open wounds."
      },
      {
        q: "Can the treatment be done in summer?",
        a: "Yes, Carbon Peeling can be done year-round. However, proper sun protection (SPF 30+) is important in the days following the treatment, especially in summer."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    id: 'pigmentation-removal',
    title: 'Pigmentation Removal',
    icon: `<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 3v1m0 16v1m9-9h-1M4 12H3m15.364 6.364l-.707-.707M6.343 6.343l-.707-.707m12.728 0l-.707.707M6.343 17.657l-.707.707M16 12a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0z" /></svg>`,
    questions: [
      {
        q: "What types of pigmentation spots can be treated with laser?",
        a: "Laser can treat: sun spots, age spots, freckles, melasma (certain types), post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation (e.g., post-acne spots), and cafe-au-lait spots. An accurate diagnosis is important before treatment, so consultation is necessary."
      },
      {
        q: "How does laser pigmentation removal work?",
        a: "The laser specifically targets cells containing pigment (melanin). High-energy light pulses break down the pigment particles, which are then naturally removed by the body's immune system. The surrounding skin remains intact."
      },
      {
        q: "How many treatments are needed?",
        a: "The number of treatments needed depends on the type, size, and depth of the pigmentation spot. Superficial spots can be removed with 1-3 treatments, deeper pigmentation may require 4-6 treatments. Treatments are performed at 4-6 week intervals."
      },
      {
        q: "Is the treatment painful?",
        a: "The treatment involves mild stinging that most patients tolerate well. The devices have built-in cooling that increases comfort. Numbing cream can be applied if needed."
      },
      {
        q: "What is the healing process like?",
        a: "Temporary darkening followed by scab formation is expected in the treated area. The scab naturally falls off within 7-14 days, revealing new, healthy skin underneath. Important: do not pick at the scab and use sunscreen!"
      },
      {
        q: "Can pigmentation spots come back?",
        a: "Successfully removed pigmentation spots generally do not return, BUT new spots can develop due to sun exposure or hormonal changes. The key to prevention is: regular use of sunscreen (SPF 30+) and avoiding excessive sun exposure."
      },
      {
        q: "Can it be done on any skin type?",
        a: "The treatment is safest and most effective on lighter skin types (Fitzpatrick I-III). On darker skin, there is a higher risk of hypopigmentation (light spots), so more cautious settings are required. We assess suitability during consultation."
      },
      {
        q: "Can melasma be treated with laser?",
        a: "Melasma is a complex problem where laser treatment is only one element of comprehensive therapy. It can be effective for some types, but may worsen others. For melasma, expert consultation and a personalized treatment plan are definitely required."
      },
      {
        q: "When is the best time for treatment?",
        a: "The autumn-winter months are ideal for pigmentation treatment when sun intensity is lower. It can also be done in summer with increased sun protection, but the risk of re-pigmentation is higher."
      },
      {
        q: "What should I do before and after the treatment?",
        a: "Before treatment: avoid sun exposure and self-tanners for 2-4 weeks. After treatment: use sunscreen (SPF 50), avoid direct sunlight, don't scratch, and moisturize regularly. Our specialist will explain the exact protocol."
      }
    ]
  }
];

// Color scheme for each category
const categoryColors: Record<string, { primary: string; light: string; bg: string; shadow: string }> = {
  'general': { primary: '#c53f75', light: '#e497a2', bg: '#fdf8f6', shadow: 'rgba(197, 63, 117, 0.15)' },
  'laser-hair-removal': { primary: '#3b82f6', light: '#93c5fd', bg: '#eff6ff', shadow: 'rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.15)' },
  'hydrabeauty': { primary: '#0d9488', light: '#5eead4', bg: '#f0fdfa', shadow: 'rgba(13, 148, 136, 0.15)' },
